look guys, another way to compile is to go on comman or MS-DOS. you can do this by going to run and typing in cmd…then press enter. then look to see where you code is (what directory), for example, if its on desktop and the folder is called testscape, then type in cd desktop\testscape int he command/MS-DOS. after that the directory should chnage now you need to see whee you jdk is. say you have the jdk1.3.0_02 and its in the directory c:\jdk1.3.0_02 then type in c:\jdk1.3.0_02\bin\javac nameofsource.java
this shoudl work…make sure your source has no errors!
